title: MUSA 5080 Portfolio
text:
This portfolio documents my learning journey in Public Policy Analytics (MUSA 5080).


Advanced spatial analysis and data science for urban planning and public policy.




Weekly Notes: My learning reflections and key concepts
Labs: Completed assignments and analyses
Final Project: Capstone modeling challenge





Name: Henry Sywulak-Herr
Background: Second-Year City Planning student concentrating in STIP. Philly (suburbs) native! Went to Penn for my Undergrad (BA Environmental Science, Minor in Chemistry).
Why I’m Taking This Course: I want to solidify the modeling background I already have, learn more about data visualization, and how these skills can be applied to a broad range of fields - but primarily transportation :)





Email: [hssherr@upenn.edu]
GitHub: [@hssherr]
